title: Tileset
data:
A **tileset** is a set of graphical tiles used in [roguelikes](/wiki/Roguelike "Roguelike") to substitute the regular [ASCII](/wiki/ASCII "ASCII") graphics, creating a [GUI](/wiki/Graphical_user_interface "Graphical user interface"). It works by defining a set graphical tile for every symbol and object in the game. Graphical tilesets are often beneficial to new roguelike players who are not accustomed to the usual graphics-free style roguelikes are presented in; *[Angband](/wiki/Angband "Angband")* in particular has exceptional support for tile customization.

The *[NetHack](/wiki/NetHack "NetHack")* [DevTeam](/wiki/DevTeam "DevTeam") has created an official tileset for their official graphical client. Using tilesets provides the same [top-down view](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Top-down_perspective "wikipedia:Top-down perspective") as ASCII graphics, and should not be confused with separate clients using 3D graphics (such as [Falcon's Eye](/wiki/Falcon%27s_Eye "Falcon's Eye")), which are a separate system entirely.

## Scaled versions

### 3.6.1

- [32x32](/wiki/File:3.6.1tiles32.png "File:3.6.1tiles32.png")

### 3.4.3

- [20x20](/wiki/Default_tileset_scaled_to_20x20 "Default tileset scaled to 20x20")

## Various tilesets

At this writing (12 Dec 2015), most third party tilesets are not updated to NetHack 3.6.0. [This program](/wiki/Tileset/tile2360.py "Tileset/tile2360.py") can convert the file, if it is in BMP format, and make it mostly usable with 3.6.0; it can also aid the author in updating his/her tileset. If a tileset is in PNG format and you are running the Windows [port](/wiki/Graphical_user_interface "Graphical user interface"), it must be converted to BMP.

### Pictographic tiles

- [Nethack Modern](https://sourceforge.net/projects/nethackmodern/) A tileset published in 2015 featuring high-resolution vector art from [game-icons.net](http://game-icons.net/) (Updated to 3.6.0)
- [The Absurd NetHack Tileset](/wiki/The_Absurd_NetHack_Tileset "The Absurd NetHack Tileset") (originally [here](http://www.aesthetictech.8m.com/Absurd.htm) but the actual files have disappeared; some sizes survive on the [Wayback Machine](http://www.archive.org/), your best bet would probably be the [Authentic Invention](http://authenticinvention.com/nethack/absurd/) website.)
- [KingHack tileset](https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/17Mv50X7FvC8U_MSzBZxZq5QPPLujH-Ix?usp=sharing/) A pixelated tileset for NetHack 3.6.0 or above. Available with two backgrounds for E-ink & regular devices. Updated 30 May 2024.
- [The RLTiles](http://rltiles.sourceforge.net/)
- [PixelHack Tiles (incomplete)](http://pixelhack.blogspot.com/)
- [NeXTSTEP tiles](/wiki/NeXTSTEP_tiles "NeXTSTEP tiles")
- [DawnHack Tiles](http://dragondeplatino.deviantart.com/art/DawnHack-NetHack-3-4-3-UnNetHack-5-1-0-416312313/) (or [16x16](https://drive.google.com/open?id=0BxBmeAnufPYyaXNoUVJRbmZsUDg) or [32x32](https://drive.google.com/open?id=0BxBmeAnufPYyeWNiWU9DTktKUTg) for NetHack 3.6.0). Also has tiles for [UnNetHack](/wiki/UnNetHack "UnNetHack").
- [Tek909s update of a lost set once found on deviant art](https://www.mediafire.com/file/7pb4mv4xjebx3x4/ScrapTek32.bmp/file) ([3.6.6](https://nethackwiki.com/wiki/File:Nevanda.png)) A detailed pixel-art tile set which has been edited and expanded for [NetHack](/wiki/NetHack "NetHack")
- [UnTekhack](http://www.mediafire.com/download/6fe7ibe2ukbfbrn/untekhack.bmp/) The edited version of a lost set for (no statues as yet) [UnNetHack](/wiki/UnNetHack "UnNetHack")

### ASCII-derivative tiles

- [Abigaba tiles](/wiki/Abigaba_tiles "Abigaba tiles")
- [NetHackANSII](https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1uZCLrgfjnpeWSfAVVbeoE8cbWD931URV?usp=drive_link) (Closest to default ASCII set, but with more recognizable/friendlier dungeon features drawn with ANSII characters).
- [Geoduck's tiles](http://www.geoduckthings.net/nhack/nhack.html) (Available for 3.6.0, older version of vanilla NetHack, [SLASH'EM](/wiki/SLASH%27EM "SLASH'EM") and [UnNetHack](/wiki/UnNetHack "UnNetHack").)
- [lagged's tiles](http://lagged.deviantart.com/art/12x20-Nethack-tileset-1308112)

## Options to set a tileset

The [option](/wiki/Option "Option") **tile\_file** sets the path to the tileset; **tile\_width** and **tile\_height** set the width and height in pixels of each tile. Default settings for **tile\_width** and **tile\_height** depend on the user interface; usually both default to either 16 or 1/40th the width of the tile map (1/40th is correct for the default tileset and most third party tilesets, but Geoduck will need to have at least **tile\_height** set).

## See also

- [List of vanilla NetHack tiles](/wiki/List_of_vanilla_NetHack_tiles "List of vanilla NetHack tiles")
- [Square](/wiki/Square "Square")

## External links

- [NetHack tileset screenshots](https://bilious.alt.org/~paxed/nhsshot/)

==Various tilesets==
At this writing (12 Dec 2015), most third party tilesets are not updated to NetHack 3.6.0. [[Tileset/tile2360.py|This program]] can convert the file, if it is in BMP format, and make it mostly usable with 3.6.0; it can also aid the author in updating his/her tileset. If a tileset is in PNG format and you are running the Windows [[Graphical user interface|port]], it must be converted to BMP.

==Options to set a tileset==
The [[option]] '''tile_file''' sets the path to the tileset; '''tile_width''' and '''tile_height''' set the width and height in pixels of each tile.  Default settings for '''tile_width''' and '''tile_height''' depend on the user interface; usually both default to either 16 or 1/40th the width of the tile map (1/40th is correct for the default tileset and most third party tilesets, but Geoduck will need to have at least '''tile_height''' set).
